  "text": "Particularly in children and young adult patients, in the absence of a head trauma, spontaneous tearing of the AC wall during games and forced physical exercises leads to the leaking of CSF and blood into the subdural space [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The amount of subdural accumulation increases over time, changing the osmotic gradient owing to the effect of subdural degradation products and fenestrated immature vessels in the subdural outer membrane [CITATION_3] .",
